  "slug": "mini-cheesecakes",
  "title": "Mini baked cheesecakes",
  "subtitle": "Individual New York-style cheesecakes in a muffin tin",
  "excerpt": "Individual baked cheesecakes on a digestive biscuit base, New York-style: dense, smooth, and vanilla-forward. Made in a muffin tin and topped with a berry or a spoonful of soured cream.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "New York-style baked cheesecake is defined by its use of cream cheese (specifically Philadelphia, since the 1870s) and a dense, barely-set filling achieved through low-temperature baking. The individual muffin-tin format became popular in American home baking from the 1990s onward as a portion-controlled alternative to the full cheesecake. This method draws on the ratio documented in Dorie Greenspan's Baking from My Home to Yours (2006) adapted for the smaller tin format.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Individual cheesecakes bake faster and more evenly than a single large cheesecake. The muffin tin format also means they unmould cleanly as individual servings with no risk of a collapsed slice. The low oven temperature is intentional: it prevents the top from cracking and keeps the filling smooth.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "type": "tip"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "All the filling ingredients must be at room temperature. Cold cream cheese beaten into a batter will leave lumps that do not smooth out during baking. Take the cream cheese and eggs out of the fridge at least 1 hour before you begin.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Biscuit bases"
            },
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "digestive-biscuits",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": "crushed to fine crumbs",
                  "quantity": 150,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "unsalted-butter",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": "melted",
                  "quantity": 60,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Filling"
            },
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "cream-cheese",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": "full-fat, at room temperature",
                  "quantity": 500,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "caster-sugar",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 150,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "eggs",
                  "unit": null,
                  "prepNote": "at room temperature",
                  "quantity": 2,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "double-cream",
                  "unit": "ml",
                  "prepNote": "at room temperature",
                  "quantity": 60,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "vanilla-extract",
                  "unit": "tsp",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 2,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "lemon-juice",
                  "unit": "tbsp",
                  "prepNote": "freshly squeezed",
                  "quantity": 1,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the bases and filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 150°C fan. Line a 12-hole muffin tin with paper cases.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mix the crushed {{digestive-biscuits}} with the melted {{unsalted-butter}}. Press 1 heaped tablespoon of biscuit mixture into each case and press down firmly.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Beat the {{cream-cheese}} and {{caster-sugar}} until smooth. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time, then the {{double-cream}}, {{vanilla-extract}}, and {{lemon-juice}} until the filling is smooth and pourable.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake and chill, 22 to 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Divide the filling evenly over the biscuit bases. Bake for 22 to 25 minutes until the edges are set and the centres still have a slight wobble.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Turn the oven off and leave the cheesecakes inside with the door ajar for 20 minutes. The gradual temperature drop prevents cracking.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Transfer to a rack to cool to room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours before removing from the cases and topping.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
